{"id": "1337636423632687197", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "702167871144591461", "author_name": "_venush", "content": "<@768826248389853234> Rlim Shaikoth is still the guy that makes me afraid every time I look back. He is a thing with a clear personality, purpose, calculation and motive. But all of those things are generally not completely revealed on the outside but hidden behind a terrifyingly ignorant appearance, when he does not express any clear emotions or reactions throughout his Story, to the point that it makes people in front of him not dare to look up because they cannot know what he is thinking with those empty eyes and empty mouth.\n\n- On one hand, Shaikoth pretends to be noble and always coaxes his \"subordinates\" (who are forced) with sweet words. But on the other hand, he complacently gives them \"privileges\" that they do not want in order to bind them to him forever, as well as secretly finds a way to devour each person when they are not on guard. To put it simply, Mr. Smith sometimes creates characters that are simple but completely unconventional, but unfortunately they die because they are too contemptuous of others.", "timestamp": "2025-02-08T04:09:35.477000+00:00", "mentions": ["768826248389853234"]}
